main event: A civilian reported observing a brilliant red object resembling a flying saucer in Englewood, Colorado on December 21, 1966.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 2 minutes,The object was described as having 3 lights with the center blinking,The object moved from NW to SE and exhibited unusual flight maneuvers,Weather conditions were reported as very clear during the sighting,No photographs or physical evidence were recorded in the report
sighted object: one brilliant red object resembling a flying saucer
witness description: Mrs. Anna K. Wede from Englewood, Colorado
